  There were reports after the game at the Dan Anyiam Stadium that the match officials and some Plateau United players were assaulted by hooligans suspected to be supporters of Heartland, who were not satisfied with the referees’ handling of the game. A senior LMC official, who pleaded anonymity, told The Guardian yesterday that the league body was studying the match commissioner’s report on the events at the stadium, adding that its findings would be made public soon. “We have to be thorough in the investigation because this is a delicate issue.  But I want to assure the teams that we will do the right thing,” he said. To enable commenting and other interactive features, please switch to the more advanced .